com.psychic_engine.cmput301w17t10.feelsappman

Class MoodEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.psychic_engine.cmput301w17t10.feelsappman.Controllers.ModelFrame
      • com.psychic_engine.cmput301w17t10.feelsappman.Models.MoodEvent

  • public class MoodEvent
extends ModelFrame
    Model class for a standard mood entry. Each mood event requires a Mood that is mandatory. Other fields such as trigger, social setting, and pictures are optional features that the participant would like to add.
    See Also:
    Mood, SocialSetting, Photograph

      • setTrigger

        public void setTrigger(java.lang.String trigger)
                throws triggerTooLongException
        Setter method to set the reason for the mood event. The reason for the mood event must be simple and short, and thus must be less than 20 character and 3 words long. Failure to meet these requirements will cause the system to reject the edit/add request for the mood event.
        Parameters:
        trigger -
        Throws:
        triggerTooLongException
